column5: Drove up Saturday and came back today. Lakes were snow covered Saturday with open areas around dams.  A few people out on Cedar, Miners Bay and Grass. Today looked worse with wet gray areas.  Few people out on Grass and Cedar.  Larger lakes don't look ready.  Ice on bay in front of cottage was 6-8 inches but mostly white ice with top part soft.  Surprised not that much snow.
It's going to be an iffy week, not really all that cold for the next while.
Thanks for the update, was curious how ice was coming along in that area
